		<title>This is how you dance (without moving)</title>
		<link>https://boingboing.net/2018/06/05/this-is-how-you-dance-without.html</link>
		<comments>https://boingboing.net/2018/06/05/this-is-how-you-dance-without.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 05 Jun 2018 17:40:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rusty Blazenhoff]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Post]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Video]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[dancing]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[magic]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[stop-motion]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://boingboing.net/?p=602151</guid>



		<description><![CDATA[<img width="600" height="338" src="https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?fit=600%2C338&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w, https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?resize=600%2C338&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?resize=930%2C523&amp;ssl=1 930w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /> <p>
<p>YouTuber <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCqNe2Mqtv5sNidn5hAAEfiQ">Ryan Higa</a> admits that he can't dance. When one of his viewers asked if he could dance without moving, he put together this amazing <a href="https://youtu.be/2s4GMLkTNv0">stop-motion video</a> with his friends.

<em>This</em> is how it was made:

https://youtu.be/6e7wxqOo7ps

<p>(<em><a href="http://www.neatorama.com/2018/06/03/Dancing-Without-Moving/">Neatorama</a></em>)]]></description>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[<img width="600" height="338" src="https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?fit=600%2C338&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w, https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?resize=600%2C338&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/dancing-without-moving.jpg?resize=930%2C523&amp;ssl=1 930w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /> <p>
<p>YouTuber <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCqNe2Mqtv5sNidn5hAAEfiQ">Ryan Higa</a> admits that he can't dance. When one of his viewers asked if he could dance without moving, he put together this amazing <a href="https://youtu.be/2s4GMLkTNv0">stop-motion video</a> with his friends.

<em>This</em> is how it was made:

